        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ærttīvyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ærttīvyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>ærttyvd</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ærttevun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>ærttivd</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>блестеть</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to glitter</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>блистать </q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to be radiant with</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сверкать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to sparkle</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сиять</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to radiate</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>светиться</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to shine</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                    <lang/>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>ærttevagæ</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>молния</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>lightning</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                    <note type="bibl">(<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1940 III
                                60</biblScope></bibl>)</note>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ærttīvy syǧzærīnaw</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>блестит как золото</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>it is shining loke gold</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"
                            /><biblScope>101</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>jæ xūd ærfældæxta je ʽrttīvag cæstytyl</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>надвинул шапку на свои сверкающие глаза</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>[he] pulled his hat over his sparkling eyes</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Æfx._Xæs."
                            /><biblScope>103</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>komæj zyng ferttyvta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>из ущелья сверкнул огонь</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>fire flashed from the gorge</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."
                            /><biblScope>194</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>stur ajdænæ ærttevæntæ kodta xormæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>большое зеркало блестело на солнце</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a big mirror was sparkling in the sun</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>119</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>bajrægutæ ærttevæntæ kaluncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>жеребята сверкают (чистотой)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>foals are spotlessly clean</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"
                            /><biblScope>271%l4%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Вместе с <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*ardēp-(ʽrdʽур)</w>
                        <gloss><q>блистать</q></gloss></mentioned> представляет, по-видимому,
                    сложение из *%iāϑr-dīp%i-, буквально „огне-блистать“; ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>ātr-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>ʽʽtr</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>art</w>
                        <gloss><q>огонь</q></gloss></mentioned>. Во второй части не %itap%i-, как
                    думает <bibl><author>Reichelt</author></bibl>, а %idīp%i-, ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>dīp-</w>
                        <gloss><q>пылать</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘сверкать’, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>dif-: dift-</w>
                        <gloss><q>загораться</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘зажигаться’. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*ardēpāk(ʽrtʽypʽk)</w>
                        <gloss><q>сияние</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘сияющий’= <mentioned
                        xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>ærttevag</w></mentioned> (%i*rōxšn ardēpāk%i = %iroxs ærttevag%i „свет
                    сияющий“). Если согдийское %iʽrδʽyp-%i возводить к %i*drafaya-%i (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Gershevitch"/><biblScope>§
                        439</biblScope></bibl>), то осетинское слово придется отделить от
                    согдийского, так как %iærttev%i- (с %itt%i!) фонетически никак не может
                    восходить к *%idrafaya%i.%n<bibl><author>Reichelt</author><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ZII"/><biblScope>IV 247</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TSP"
                            /><biblScope>235</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Together with <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*ardēp-(ʽrdʽур)</w>
                        <gloss><q>to shine</q></gloss></mentioned> the word of interest represents
                    apparently the composition of %i*āϑr%i-%idīp%i-, which literally means ‘to
                    fire-shine’, compare <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>ātr-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>ʽʽtr</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>art</w>
                        <gloss><q>fire</q></gloss></mentioned>. It is not %itap%i- in the second
                    part as <bibl><author>Reichelt</author></bibl>supposes, but %idīp%i-, compare
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>dīp-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to blaze</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘to sparkle’, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>dif-: dift-</w>
                        <gloss><q>to blaze up</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘to light up’. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*ardēpāk(ʽrtʽypʽk)</w>
                        <gloss><q>radiance</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘radiant’= <mentioned
                        xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>ærttevag</w></mentioned> (%i*rōxšn ardēpāk%i = %iroxs ærttevag%i 'shining
                    light'). If one traces Sogdian %iʽrδʽyp-%i back to %i*drafaya-%i (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Gershevitch"/><biblScope>§
                        439</biblScope></bibl>), then the Ossetic word has to be separated from the
                    Sogdian one because %iærttev%i- (with %itt%i!) cannot trace back to *%idrafaya%i
                            phonetically.%n<bibl><author>Reichelt</author><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ZII"/><biblScope>IV 247</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TSP"
                            /><biblScope>235</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
